# ============================================================
# PROJECT INIT FILE — IoMT Anomaly Detection System
# ============================================================
# This file is the single source of truth for all agents.
# Read this COMPLETELY before touching any file in the project.
# ============================================================

PROJECT: IoMT (Internet of Medical Things) Anomaly Detection System
OBJECTIVE: Build a production-grade multi-model AI system for real-time anomaly detection in medical IoT devices
STATUS: In Progress — Core models (TFT, CNN) will be trained on Kaggle and provided later

# ============================================================
# SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW
# ============================================================

This is a MODULAR, PARALLEL-EXECUTABLE system with 3 AI models:

1. TFT (Temporal Fusion Transformer) — Time-series forecasting
   - INPUT: sequence_length = 30 timesteps
   - FEATURES: [heart_rate, temperature] (2 features only)
   - OUTPUT: anomaly score [0.0-1.0]
   - STATUS: Will be trained on Kaggle, model file provided later

2. CNN (ResNet50) — Image classification
   - INPUT: 224x224 RGB image
   - OUTPUT: anomaly score [0.0-1.0]
   - STATUS: Will be trained on Kaggle, model file provided later

3. Edge Model (Isolation Forest) — Real-time anomaly detection
   - INPUT: single row vector [heart_rate, temperature]
   - OUTPUT: anomaly score [0.0-1.0]
   - STATUS: To be trained locally by agents

These models run INDEPENDENTLY and their outputs are FUSED to produce a final decision.

The system supports:
- Core models (TFT, CNN): Pre-trained on Kaggle, deployed locally
- Edge model: Trained locally on processed data
- Real-time inference (local CPU/edge device)
- REST API deployment (FastAPI)
- Parallel agent execution (multiple agents can work simultaneously)

# ============================================================
# MODEL INPUT SPECIFICATIONS (CRITICAL - DO NOT DEVIATE)
# ============================================================

TFT MODEL:
──────────
Input shape: (batch_size, 30, 2)
  - 30 = sequence length (last 30 timesteps)
  - 2 = features [heart_rate, temperature]
Features:
  - heart_rate: float, range [40-200] bpm
  - temperature: float, range [35-42] Celsius
Preprocessing:
  - Z-score normalization per feature
  - No missing values allowed
Output:
  - anomaly_score: float [0.0-1.0]

CNN MODEL:
──────────
Input shape: (batch_size, 3, 224, 224)
  - 3 = RGB channels
  - 224x224 = image dimensions
Preprocessing:
  - Resize to 224x224
  - Normalize: mean=[0.485, 0.456, 0.406], std=[0.229, 0.224, 0.225] (ImageNet stats)
Output:
  - anomaly_score: float [0.0-1.0]

EDGE MODEL:
───────────
Input shape: (1, 2)
  - Single row vector
  - 2 = features [heart_rate, temperature]
Features:
  - heart_rate: float, range [40-200] bpm
  - temperature: float, range [35-42] Celsius
Preprocessing:
  - Same Z-score normalization as TFT (use same scaler)
Output:
  - anomaly_score: float [0.0-1.0]

# ============================================================
# PARALLEL WORK PLAN — AGENT TASK ASSIGNMENTS
# ============================================================
# Each task is numbered and can be executed in parallel.
# Dependencies are clearly marked.
# Agents should claim a task number and work independently.
# ============================================================

PHASE 1: FOUNDATION (No dependencies - all parallel)
═════════════════════════════════════════════════════

TASK 1: Create config.py
─────────────────────────
AGENT: Config Agent
DEPENDENCIES: None
PRIORITY: HIGH (other tasks need this)
DELIVERABLE: config.py

Contents:
- All file paths (data/, models/, images/, logs/)
- Model hyperparameters (sequence_length=30, features=[heart_rate, temp])
- Fusion weights (w_tft=0.4, w_cnn=0.3, w_edge=0.3)
- Thresholds (NORMAL_THRESHOLD=0.4, CRITICAL_THRESHOLD=0.7)
- Logging configuration
- API configuration (host, port)
- Normalization parameters (mean, std for each feature)

TASK 2: Create requirements.txt
────────────────────────────────
AGENT: Dependencies Agent
DEPENDENCIES: None
PRIORITY: HIGH
DELIVERABLE: requirements.txt

Include all packages listed in ENVIRONMENT section below.

TASK 3: Create directory structure
───────────────────────────────────
AGENT: Structure Agent
DEPENDENCIES: None
PRIORITY: HIGH
DELIVERABLE: Create folders if not exist:
- data/
- data/logs/
- models/
- images/ (optional)

TASK 4: Create __init__.py files
─────────────────────────────────
AGENT: Structure Agent
DEPENDENCIES: None
PRIORITY: MEDIUM
DELIVERABLE: Empty __init__.py in:
- data_pipeline/__init__.py
- tft_model/__init__.py
- cnn_model/__init__.py
- edge_model/__init__.py
- fusion/__init__.py
- api/__init__.py

═════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PHASE 2: DATA PIPELINE (Sequential within, parallel to other phases)
═════════════════════════════════════════════════════

TASK 5: data_pipeline/load_data.py
───────────────────────────────────
AGENT: Data Pipeline Agent 1
DEPENDENCIES: TASK 1 (config.py)
PRIORITY: HIGH
DELIVERABLE: data_pipeline/load_data.py

Functionality:
- Read healthcare_iot_target_dataset.csv
- Validate columns: heart_rate, temperature, timestamp
- Handle missing values (forward fill)
- Save to data/raw_loaded.csv
- CLI: --input <path> --output <path>
- Logging to data/logs/data_pipeline.log

TASK 6: data_pipeline/preprocess.py
────────────────────────────────────
AGENT: Data Pipeline Agent 2
DEPENDENCIES: TASK 1 (config.py), TASK 5 (load_data.py must be done first)
PRIORITY: HIGH
DELIVERABLE: data_pipeline/preprocess.py

Functionality:
- Read data/raw_loaded.csv
- Extract ONLY heart_rate and temperature columns
- Z-score normalization (calculate mean, std, save to config or pickle)
- Sort by timestamp
- Create sequences of length 30 (sliding window)
- Save to data/preprocessed.csv
- CLI: --input <path> --output <path>
- Logging to data/logs/data_pipeline.log

TASK 7: data_pipeline/save_processed.py
────────────────────────────────────────
AGENT: Data Pipeline Agent 3
DEPENDENCIES: TASK 6 (preprocess.py must be done first)
PRIORITY: HIGH
DELIVERABLE: data_pipeline/save_processed.py

Functionality:
- Read data/preprocessed.csv
- Final validation (check shape, no NaN, correct columns)
- Save to data/processed_vitals.csv ← SHARED ARTIFACT
- Log statistics (mean, std, min, max, count)
- CLI: --input <path> --output <path>
- Logging to data/logs/data_pipeline.log

═════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PHASE 3: MODEL INFERENCE MODULES (All parallel)
═════════════════════════════════════════════════════

TASK 8: tft_model/inference.py
───────────────────────────────
AGENT: TFT Agent
DEPENDENCIES: TASK 1 (config.py)
PRIORITY: HIGH
DELIVERABLE: tft_model/inference.py

Functionality:
- Load models/tft_model.pth (will be provided later from Kaggle)
- Input: numpy array shape (30, 2) or CSV with 30 rows
- Preprocess: apply same normalization as training
- Predict: anomaly score [0.0-1.0]
- CLI: --model <path> --input <path> --output <path>
- Function: def predict_tft(input_data) -> float
- Logging to data/logs/tft_inference.log

NOTE: Model file will be provided later. For now, create inference code
that assumes model exists. Add error handling if model not found.

TASK 9: cnn_model/inference.py
───────────────────────────────
AGENT: CNN Agent
DEPENDENCIES: TASK 1 (config.py)
PRIORITY: HIGH
DELIVERABLE: cnn_model/inference.py

Functionality:
- Load models/cnn_model.pth (will be provided later from Kaggle)
- Input: image path (JPG/PNG)
- Preprocess: resize to 224x224, normalize (ImageNet stats)
- Predict: anomaly score [0.0-1.0]
- CLI: --model <path> --input <image_path> --output <path>
- Function: def predict_cnn(image_path) -> float
- Logging to data/logs/cnn_inference.log

NOTE: Model file will be provided later. For now, create inference code
that assumes model exists. Add error handling if model not found.

TASK 10: edge_model/isolation_forest.py
────────────────────────────────────────
AGENT: Edge Model Agent
DEPENDENCIES: TASK 1 (config.py), TASK 7 (processed data)
PRIORITY: HIGH
DELIVERABLE: edge_model/isolation_forest.py

Functionality:
TWO MODES:

1. TRAINING MODE (--mode train):
   - Load data/processed_vitals.csv
   - Extract heart_rate and temperature columns
   - Train IsolationForest (n_estimators=100, contamination=0.1)
   - Save models/isolation_forest.pkl
   - Save scaler (same as preprocessing) to models/scaler.pkl
   - Logging to data/logs/edge_training.log

2. INFERENCE MODE (--mode infer):
   - Load models/isolation_forest.pkl
   - Input: single row [heart_rate, temperature]
   - Preprocess: apply scaler
   - Predict: anomaly score [0.0-1.0]
   - Return: float

CLI:
  Training:  --data <path> --mode train --output models/isolation_forest.pkl
  Inference: --data <path> --mode infer --model <path>

Function: def predict_edge(input_row) -> float

═════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PHASE 4: FUSION & API (Depends on Phase 3)
═════════════════════════════════════════════════════

TASK 11: fusion/fusion_logic.py
────────────────────────────────
AGENT: Fusion Agent
DEPENDENCIES: TASK 1 (config.py)
PRIORITY: MEDIUM
DELIVERABLE: fusion/fusion_logic.py

Functionality:
- Input: tft_score, cnn_score, edge_score (floats 0-1)
- Load weights from config.py
- Calculate weighted average
- Apply thresholds (NORMAL/SUSPICIOUS/CRITICAL)
- Calculate confidence (based on score variance)
- Return dict with all scores + decision
- CLI: --tft <float> --cnn <float> --edge <float>
- Function: def fuse(tft_score, cnn_score, edge_score) -> dict
- Logging to data/logs/fusion.log

Output format:
{
  "tft_score": 0.35,
  "cnn_score": 0.42,
  "edge_score": 0.28,
  "final_score": 0.36,
  "decision": "NORMAL",
  "confidence": 0.92,
  "timestamp": "2026-04-18T10:30:45Z"
}

TASK 12: api/main.py
────────────────────
AGENT: API Agent
DEPENDENCIES: TASK 1, TASK 8, TASK 9, TASK 10, TASK 11
PRIORITY: MEDIUM
DELIVERABLE: api/main.py

Functionality:
- FastAPI application
- Load all 3 models on startup (cache in memory)
- Endpoint: POST /predict
  - Input: {"vitals": {"heart_rate": float, "temperature": float, "history": [...]}, "image_path": str}
  - Call tft_model/inference.py
  - Call cnn_model/inference.py (if image provided)
  - Call edge_model/isolation_forest.py
  - Call fusion/fusion_logic.py
  - Return JSON response
- Endpoint: GET /health
  - Check if models loaded
  - Return status
- Endpoint: POST /models/reload
  - Reload models from disk
- Logging to data/logs/api_requests.log
- CLI: uvicorn api.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000

═════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PHASE 5: ORCHESTRATION (Depends on all above)
═════════════════════════════════════════════════════

TASK 13: run_all.py
───────────────────
AGENT: Orchestrator Agent
DEPENDENCIES: ALL TASKS ABOVE
PRIORITY: LOW
DELIVERABLE: run_all.py

Functionality:
- Run all components in sequence or parallel
- MODES:
  1. Sequential: run data pipeline → train edge model → start API
  2. Parallel: train edge model in background, start API
  3. Inference only: skip training, just start API
- CLI: --mode sequential|parallel|inference
- Use subprocess or multiprocessing
- Logging to data/logs/orchestrator.log

═════════════════════════════════════════════════════
TASK DEPENDENCY GRAPH
═════════════════════════════════════════════════════

TASK 1 (config.py) ──┬──► TASK 5 (load_data.py)
                     │
TASK 2 (requirements)│
                     │
TASK 3 (directories) │
                     │
TASK 4 (__init__)    │
                     │
                     ├──► TASK 6 (preprocess.py) ──► TASK 7 (save_processed.py)
                     │                                        │
                     ├──► TASK 8 (tft inference)             │
                     │                                        │
                     ├──► TASK 9 (cnn inference)             │
                     │                                        │
                     └──► TASK 10 (edge model) ◄─────────────┘
                              │
                              ├──► TASK 11 (fusion)
                              │
                              └──► TASK 12 (api)
                                        │
                                        └──► TASK 13 (run_all)

═════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PARALLEL EXECUTION STRATEGY
═════════════════════════════════════════════════════

WAVE 1 (Start immediately, no dependencies):
  - TASK 1, 2, 3, 4 (can all run in parallel)

WAVE 2 (After TASK 1 completes):
  - TASK 5 (data pipeline start)
  - TASK 8 (tft inference - can start even without data)
  - TASK 9 (cnn inference - can start even without data)
  - TASK 11 (fusion - can start even without models)

WAVE 3 (After TASK 5 completes):
  - TASK 6 (preprocess)

WAVE 4 (After TASK 6 completes):
  - TASK 7 (save processed)

WAVE 5 (After TASK 7 completes):
  - TASK 10 (edge model training)

WAVE 6 (After TASK 8, 9, 10, 11 complete):
  - TASK 12 (api)

WAVE 7 (After TASK 12 completes):
  - TASK 13 (orchestrator)

ESTIMATED TIME:
  - WAVE 1: 10 minutes (4 agents in parallel)
  - WAVE 2: 15 minutes (4 agents in parallel)
  - WAVE 3: 10 minutes (1 agent)
  - WAVE 4: 5 minutes (1 agent)
  - WAVE 5: 20 minutes (1 agent, model training)
  - WAVE 6: 15 minutes (1 agent)
  - WAVE 7: 10 minutes (1 agent)
  - TOTAL: ~85 minutes (with parallelization)
  - TOTAL: ~150 minutes (without parallelization)

Each folder is owned by a specific agent/module.
Agents can work in parallel. Each module is fully independent.

project_root/
│
├── data_pipeline/          # ═══ AGENT: Data Pipeline ═══
│   │                       # RESPONSIBILITY: ETL for raw medical data
│   │                       # INPUT: healthcare_iot_target_dataset.csv (raw)
│   │                       # OUTPUT: data/processed_vitals.csv
│   │
│   ├── __init__.py         # Makes this a Python package
│   ├── load_data.py        # Load raw PhysioNet/IoMT dataset from CSV/API
│   │                       # - Read healthcare_iot_target_dataset.csv
│   │                       # - Validate columns: heart_rate, spo2, temp, bp_sys, bp_dia, timestamp
│   │                       # - Handle missing values (forward fill for time-series)
│   │                       # - CLI: --input <path> --output <path>
│   │
│   ├── preprocess.py       # Normalize and engineer features
│   │                       # - Z-score normalization (mean=0, std=1)
│   │                       # - Create rolling windows (5-min, 15-min averages)
│   │                       # - Detect outliers (IQR method)
│   │                       # - Convert to time-series format (timestamp sorted)
│   │                       # - CLI: --input <path> --output <path>
│   │
│   └── save_processed.py   # Save final processed data
│                           # - Save as data/processed_vitals.csv
│                           # - Log statistics (mean, std, missing %)
│                           # - CLI: --input <path> --output <path>
│
├── tft_model/              # ═══ AGENT: TFT Model ═══
│   │                       # RESPONSIBILITY: Time-series forecasting & anomaly detection
│   │                       # INPUT: data/processed_vitals.csv
│   │                       # OUTPUT: models/tft_model.pth
│   │
│   ├── __init__.py         # Makes this a Python package
│   ├── dataset.py          # PyTorch Dataset class for TFT
│   │                       # - TimeSeriesDataset(torch.utils.data.Dataset)
│   │                       # - Sliding window: 60 timesteps input → 10 timesteps forecast
│   │                       # - Features: heart_rate, spo2, temp, bp_sys, bp_dia
│   │                       # - Target: next 10 timesteps of all features
│   │                       # - Return: (input_tensor, target_tensor, timestamp)
│   │
│   ├── train.py            # Train Temporal Fusion Transformer
│   │                       # - Load data/processed_vitals.csv
│   │                       # - Split: 70% train, 15% val, 15% test
│   │                       # - Model: pytorch-forecasting TemporalFusionTransformer
│   │                       # - Hyperparams: hidden_size=64, attention_heads=4, dropout=0.1
│   │                       # - Loss: QuantileLoss (for uncertainty estimation)
│   │                       # - Epochs: 50 (early stopping patience=10)
│   │                       # - Save: models/tft_model.pth
│   │                       # - Log: training loss, validation loss, MAE, RMSE
│   │                       # - CLI: --data <path> --epochs <int> --batch_size <int>
│   │
│   └── inference.py        # Load model and predict anomaly score
│                           # - Load models/tft_model.pth
│                           # - Input: 60 timesteps of vitals (numpy array or CSV)
│                           # - Predict: next 10 timesteps
│                           # - Anomaly score = MAE between predicted vs actual (if available)
│                           # - If no actual: use prediction uncertainty (quantile range)
│                           # - Return: float 0.0–1.0 (0=normal, 1=anomaly)
│                           # - CLI: --model <path> --input <path> --output <path>
│
├── cnn_model/              # ═══ AGENT: CNN Model ═══
│   │                       # RESPONSIBILITY: Image classification for medical imaging
│   │                       # INPUT: images/ (X-rays, ECG plots, thermal images)
│   │                       # OUTPUT: models/cnn_model.pth
│   │
│   ├── __init__.py         # Makes this a Python package
│   ├── model.py            # ResNet50 transfer learning definition
│   │                       # - Load pretrained ResNet50 (ImageNet weights)
│   │                       # - Replace final FC layer: 1000 → 3 classes (NORMAL, SUSPICIOUS, CRITICAL)
│   │                       # - Freeze first 3 blocks, fine-tune last 2 blocks
│   │                       # - Input: 224x224 RGB image
│   │                       # - Output: 3-class logits
│   │                       # - Activation: Softmax for probabilities
│   │
│   ├── train.py            # Fine-tune on medical images
│   │                       # - Load images from images/ directory
│   │                       # - Augmentation: RandomHorizontalFlip, RandomRotation(10°), ColorJitter
│   │                       # - Split: 80% train, 20% val
│   │                       # - Loss: CrossEntropyLoss
│   │                       # - Optimizer: Adam (lr=1e-4)
│   │                       # - Epochs: 30 (early stopping patience=5)
│   │                       # - Save: models/cnn_model.pth
│   │                       # - Log: accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score
│   │                       # - CLI: --data <image_dir> --epochs <int> --batch_size <int>
│   │
│   └── inference.py        # Load model and classify image
│                           # - Load models/cnn_model.pth
│                           # - Input: single image path (JPG/PNG)
│                           # - Preprocess: resize to 224x224, normalize (ImageNet stats)
│                           # - Predict: class probabilities [p_normal, p_suspicious, p_critical]
│                           # - Anomaly score = p_suspicious * 0.5 + p_critical * 1.0
│                           # - Return: float 0.0–1.0
│                           # - CLI: --model <path> --input <image_path>
│
├── edge_model/             # ═══ AGENT: Edge Model ═══
│   │                       # RESPONSIBILITY: Real-time anomaly detection (lightweight)
│   │                       # INPUT: data/processed_vitals.csv (for training)
│   │                       # OUTPUT: models/isolation_forest.pkl
│   │
│   ├── __init__.py         # Makes this a Python package
│   └── isolation_forest.py # Train and infer with Isolation Forest
│                           # TRAINING MODE:
│                           # - Load data/processed_vitals.csv
│                           # - Features: heart_rate, spo2, temp, bp_sys, bp_dia
│                           # - Model: sklearn.ensemble.IsolationForest
│                           # - Hyperparams: n_estimators=100, contamination=0.1, max_samples=256
│                           # - Fit on normal data only (filter out labeled anomalies if available)
│                           # - Save: models/isolation_forest.pkl
│                           # - CLI: --data <path> --mode train
│                           #
│                           # INFERENCE MODE:
│                           # - Load models/isolation_forest.pkl
│                           # - Input: single row of vitals (5 features)
│                           # - Predict: anomaly score (decision_function output)
│                           # - Normalize to 0.0–1.0 range
│                           # - Return: float 0.0–1.0
│                           # - CLI: --data <path> --mode infer --model <path>
│
├── fusion/                 # ═══ AGENT: Fusion Engine ═══
│   │                       # RESPONSIBILITY: Combine all model outputs into final decision
│   │                       # INPUT: tft_score, cnn_score, edge_score (floats 0–1)
│   │                       # OUTPUT: decision (NORMAL/SUSPICIOUS/CRITICAL)
│   │
│   ├── __init__.py         # Makes this a Python package
│   └── fusion_logic.py     # Weighted fusion algorithm
│                           # FUSION ALGORITHM:
│                           # - Weighted average: final_score = w1*tft + w2*cnn + w3*edge
│                           # - Default weights: w1=0.4, w2=0.3, w3=0.3 (configurable in config.py)
│                           # - Thresholds:
│                           #     final_score < 0.4   → NORMAL
│                           #     0.4 ≤ score < 0.7   → SUSPICIOUS
│                           #     final_score ≥ 0.7   → CRITICAL
│                           # - Return: dict with all scores + final decision
│                           # - CLI: --tft <float> --cnn <float> --edge <float>
│                           # - Function signature:
│                           #     def fuse(tft_score, cnn_score, edge_score, weights=None):
│                           #         return {"tft": tft_score, "cnn": cnn_score, "edge": edge_score,
│                           #                 "final": final_score, "decision": decision}
│
├── api/                    # ═══ AGENT: API Server ═══
│   │                       # RESPONSIBILITY: REST API for real-time predictions
│   │                       # INPUT: HTTP POST request with vitals + optional image
│   │                       # OUTPUT: JSON response with fused decision
│   │
│   ├── __init__.py         # Makes this a Python package
│   └── main.py             # FastAPI application
│                           # ENDPOINTS:
│                           # 1. POST /predict
│                           #    - Request body: {"vitals": {...}, "image_path": "..."}
│                           #    - Load all 3 models (TFT, CNN, Edge)
│                           #    - Run inference on each model
│                           #    - Call fusion/fusion_logic.py
│                           #    - Return JSON response
│                           # 2. GET /health
│                           #    - Return {"status": "ok", "models_loaded": true/false}
│                           # 3. GET /models/reload
│                           #    - Reload all models from disk
│                           #
│                           # STARTUP:
│                           # - Load models on startup (cache in memory)
│                           # - Validate models exist, log warnings if missing
│                           #
│                           # ERROR HANDLING:
│                           # - 400 Bad Request: invalid input format
│                           # - 500 Internal Server Error: model inference failure
│                           #
│                           # LOGGING:
│                           # - Log every request: timestamp, input, output, latency
│                           #
│                           # CLI: uvicorn api.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
│
├── models/                 # ═══ MODEL ARTIFACTS (created by agents) ═══
│   ├── tft_model.pth       # TFT PyTorch model (created by tft_model/train.py)
│   ├── cnn_model.pth       # CNN PyTorch model (created by cnn_model/train.py)
│   └── isolation_forest.pkl # Isolation Forest sklearn model (created by edge_model/)
│
├── data/                   # ═══ DATA ARTIFACTS (created by agents) ═══
│   ├── processed_vitals.csv # Processed time-series data (created by data_pipeline/)
│   └── logs/               # Training logs, inference logs
│
├── images/                 # ═══ IMAGE DATA (optional, for CNN training) ═══
│   ├── normal/             # Normal medical images
│   ├── suspicious/         # Suspicious medical images
│   └── critical/           # Critical medical images
│
├── config.py               # ═══ SHARED CONFIGURATION ═══
│                           # All agents read from this file. DO NOT HARDCODE VALUES.
│                           # Contains:
│                           # - File paths (data/, models/, images/)
│                           # - Model hyperparameters (epochs, batch_size, learning_rate)
│                           # - Fusion weights (w1, w2, w3)
│                           # - Thresholds (normal_threshold, critical_threshold)
│                           # - Logging config (log level, log file path)
│                           # - API config (host, port)
│
├── requirements.txt        # ═══ PYTHON DEPENDENCIES ═══
│                           # All packages needed for the project
│                           # Install: pip install -r requirements.txt
│
├── run_all.py              # ═══ ORCHESTRATOR ═══
│                           # Run all components in sequence or parallel
│                           # MODES:
│                           # 1. Sequential: python run_all.py --mode sequential
│                           #    - Run data_pipeline → train models → start API
│                           # 2. Parallel: python run_all.py --mode parallel
│                           #    - Use multiprocessing to train models in parallel
│                           # 3. Inference only: python run_all.py --mode inference
│                           #    - Skip training, just start API with existing models
│
└── healthcare_iot_target_dataset.csv  # ═══ RAW DATA (provided) ═══
                            # Original dataset with raw vital signs

# ============================================================
# DATA FLOW (read this carefully)
# ============================================================

PHASE 1: DATA PREPARATION
──────────────────────────
healthcare_iot_target_dataset.csv (RAW)
   │
   ├──► data_pipeline/load_data.py
   │    - Read CSV
   │    - Validate schema
   │    - Handle missing values
   │    - Output: data/raw_loaded.csv
   │
   ├──► data_pipeline/preprocess.py
   │    - Input: data/raw_loaded.csv
   │    - Normalize features (Z-score)
   │    - Create rolling windows
   │    - Sort by timestamp
   │    - Output: data/preprocessed.csv
   │
   └──► data_pipeline/save_processed.py
        - Input: data/preprocessed.csv
        - Final validation
        - Output: data/processed_vitals.csv ← SHARED ARTIFACT

PHASE 2: MODEL TRAINING (can run in parallel)
──────────────────────────────────────────────
data/processed_vitals.csv
   │
   ├──► tft_model/train.py
   │    - Load processed data
   │    - Create TimeSeriesDataset
   │    - Train TemporalFusionTransformer
   │    - Validate on test set
   │    - Output: models/tft_model.pth ← SHARED ARTIFACT
   │    - Log: data/logs/tft_training.log
   │
   ├──► edge_model/isolation_forest.py --mode train
   │    - Load processed data
   │    - Filter normal samples only
   │    - Train IsolationForest
   │    - Output: models/isolation_forest.pkl ← SHARED ARTIFACT
   │    - Log: data/logs/edge_training.log
   │
   └──► cnn_model/train.py (if images available)
        - Load images from images/ directory
        - Create ImageDataset
        - Fine-tune ResNet50
        - Validate on test set
        - Output: models/cnn_model.pth ← SHARED ARTIFACT
        - Log: data/logs/cnn_training.log

PHASE 3: INFERENCE (real-time prediction)
──────────────────────────────────────────
USER REQUEST → POST /predict
   │
   │  Request body:
   │  {
   │    "vitals": {
   │      "heart_rate": 85.0,
   │      "spo2": 96.0,
   │      "temperature": 37.2,
   │      "systolic_bp": 120.0,
   │      "diastolic_bp": 80.0
   │    },
   │    "image_path": "path/to/image.jpg"  // optional
   │  }
   │
   ├──► api/main.py receives request
   │
   ├──► tft_model/inference.py
   │    - Load models/tft_model.pth
   │    - Input: last 60 timesteps of vitals
   │    - Predict: next 10 timesteps
   │    - Calculate anomaly score (MAE or uncertainty)
   │    - Output: tft_score (float 0.0–1.0)
   │
   ├──► cnn_model/inference.py (if image provided)
   │    - Load models/cnn_model.pth
   │    - Input: image_path
   │    - Preprocess image (resize, normalize)
   │    - Predict: class probabilities
   │    - Calculate anomaly score
   │    - Output: cnn_score (float 0.0–1.0)
   │
   ├──► edge_model/isolation_forest.py --mode infer
   │    - Load models/isolation_forest.pkl
   │    - Input: current vitals (5 features)
   │    - Predict: anomaly score
   │    - Normalize to 0–1 range
   │    - Output: edge_score (float 0.0–1.0)
   │
   ├──► fusion/fusion_logic.py
   │    - Input: tft_score, cnn_score, edge_score
   │    - Calculate weighted average
   │    - Apply thresholds
   │    - Output: {
   │        "tft_score": 0.35,
   │        "cnn_score": 0.42,
   │        "edge_score": 0.28,
   │        "final_score": 0.36,
   │        "decision": "NORMAL"
   │      }
   │
   └──► api/main.py returns JSON response

PHASE 4: LOGGING & MONITORING
──────────────────────────────
Every component logs to data/logs/:
   - data/logs/api_requests.log       (all API calls)
   - data/logs/tft_inference.log      (TFT predictions)
   - data/logs/cnn_inference.log      (CNN predictions)
   - data/logs/edge_inference.log     (Edge predictions)
   - data/logs/fusion.log             (fusion decisions)

# ============================================================
# SHARED ARTIFACTS (written by one agent, read by others)
# ============================================================

File/Artifact                     Written By                      Read By                         Format          Size (approx)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
data/processed_vitals.csv         data_pipeline/save_processed    tft_model, edge_model           CSV             ~10-100 MB
models/tft_model.pth              tft_model/train.py              tft_model/inference.py, api     PyTorch         ~50-200 MB
models/cnn_model.pth              cnn_model/train.py              cnn_model/inference.py, api     PyTorch         ~90-100 MB
models/isolation_forest.pkl       edge_model/isolation_forest     edge_model/inference, api       Pickle          ~1-5 MB
config.py                         Human/Orchestrator              ALL AGENTS                      Python          ~5 KB
data/logs/*.log                   ALL AGENTS                      Monitoring tools                Text            Growing

CRITICAL RULES FOR SHARED ARTIFACTS:
────────────────────────────────────
1. NEVER modify a shared artifact created by another agent
2. ALWAYS check if artifact exists before reading (use try/except or os.path.exists)
3. ALWAYS log when you write a shared artifact
4. ALWAYS validate artifact format before using it
5. If artifact is missing, log error and exit gracefully (don't crash)
6. Use file locks if writing to shared logs (to prevent race conditions)

# ============================================================
# CLI INTERFACE — every script must support this
# ============================================================

ALL scripts must accept command-line arguments using argparse.
ALL scripts must have --help flag that explains usage.
ALL scripts must validate inputs before processing.
ALL scripts must log to data/logs/<module_name>.log

DATA PIPELINE:
──────────────
python data_pipeline/load_data.py \
    --input healthcare_iot_target_dataset.csv \
    --output data/raw_loaded.csv \
    --log_level INFO

python data_pipeline/preprocess.py \
    --input data/raw_loaded.csv \
    --output data/preprocessed.csv \
    --normalize zscore \
    --window_size 5

python data_pipeline/save_processed.py \
    --input data/preprocessed.csv \
    --output data/processed_vitals.csv \
    --validate

TFT MODEL:
──────────
python tft_model/train.py \
    --data data/processed_vitals.csv \
    --output models/tft_model.pth \
    --epochs 50 \
    --batch_size 64 \
    --learning_rate 0.001 \
    --early_stopping_patience 10 \
    --hidden_size 64 \
    --attention_heads 4

python tft_model/inference.py \
    --model models/tft_model.pth \
    --input data/sample_vitals.csv \
    --output predictions.json \
    --return_uncertainty

CNN MODEL:
──────────
python cnn_model/train.py \
    --data images/ \
    --output models/cnn_model.pth \
    --epochs 30 \
    --batch_size 32 \
    --learning_rate 0.0001 \
    --pretrained \
    --freeze_layers 3

python cnn_model/inference.py \
    --model models/cnn_model.pth \
    --input images/test/sample.jpg \
    --output prediction.json

EDGE MODEL:
───────────
# Training mode
python edge_model/isolation_forest.py \
    --data data/processed_vitals.csv \
    --mode train \
    --output models/isolation_forest.pkl \
    --n_estimators 100 \
    --contamination 0.1

# Inference mode
python edge_model/isolation_forest.py \
    --data data/sample_vitals.csv \
    --mode infer \
    --model models/isolation_forest.pkl \
    --output prediction.json

FUSION:
───────
python fusion/fusion_logic.py \
    --tft_score 0.35 \
    --cnn_score 0.42 \
    --edge_score 0.28 \
    --weights 0.4,0.3,0.3 \
    --output decision.json

API:
────
# Start server
uvicorn api.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --reload

# Or using Python
python api/main.py --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000

ORCHESTRATOR:
─────────────
# Run everything sequentially
python run_all.py --mode sequential

# Run model training in parallel
python run_all.py --mode parallel --workers 3

# Skip training, just start API
python run_all.py --mode inference

# Full pipeline with custom config
python run_all.py --mode sequential --config custom_config.py

# ============================================================
# FUSION DECISION LOGIC (DETAILED)
# ============================================================

STEP 1: SCORE NORMALIZATION
────────────────────────────
All model outputs must be normalized to [0.0, 1.0] range:
- 0.0 = completely normal
- 1.0 = definite anomaly

TFT Score Calculation:
  - If ground truth available: MAE (Mean Absolute Error) between predicted and actual
  - If no ground truth: Use prediction uncertainty (quantile range from QuantileLoss)
  - Normalize: score = min(MAE / threshold, 1.0) where threshold = 10.0

CNN Score Calculation:
  - Get class probabilities: [p_normal, p_suspicious, p_critical]
  - score = (0.0 * p_normal) + (0.5 * p_suspicious) + (1.0 * p_critical)
  - Already in [0.0, 1.0] range

Edge Score Calculation:
  - IsolationForest returns decision_function (negative = anomaly)
  - Normalize: score = 1 / (1 + exp(decision_function))  # Sigmoid
  - Maps to [0.0, 1.0] range

STEP 2: WEIGHTED FUSION
────────────────────────
Default weights (configurable in config.py):
  w_tft = 0.4   # Time-series patterns (most important for vitals)
  w_cnn = 0.3   # Visual patterns (if image provided)
  w_edge = 0.3  # Real-time anomaly detection

If no image provided:
  w_tft = 0.6
  w_edge = 0.4
  w_cnn = 0.0

Formula:
  final_score = (w_tft * tft_score) + (w_cnn * cnn_score) + (w_edge * edge_score)

STEP 3: THRESHOLD APPLICATION
──────────────────────────────
Thresholds (configurable in config.py):
  NORMAL_THRESHOLD = 0.4
  CRITICAL_THRESHOLD = 0.7

Decision logic:
  if final_score < NORMAL_THRESHOLD:
      decision = "NORMAL"
      action = "No action required"
      color = "green"
  
  elif NORMAL_THRESHOLD <= final_score < CRITICAL_THRESHOLD:
      decision = "SUSPICIOUS"
      action = "Monitor closely, notify nurse"
      color = "yellow"
  
  else:  # final_score >= CRITICAL_THRESHOLD
      decision = "CRITICAL"
      action = "IMMEDIATE ALERT to doctor"
      color = "red"

STEP 4: CONFIDENCE CALCULATION
───────────────────────────────
Calculate confidence based on score variance:
  variance = std([tft_score, cnn_score, edge_score])
  confidence = 1.0 - min(variance * 2, 1.0)

High confidence: all models agree (low variance)
Low confidence: models disagree (high variance)

STEP 5: OUTPUT FORMAT
──────────────────────
Return dictionary:
{
  "tft_score": 0.35,
  "cnn_score": 0.42,
  "edge_score": 0.28,
  "final_score": 0.36,
  "decision": "NORMAL",
  "confidence": 0.92,
  "action": "No action required",
  "timestamp": "2026-04-18T10:30:45Z",
  "weights_used": {"tft": 0.4, "cnn": 0.3, "edge": 0.3}
}

# ============================================================
# API CONTRACT (DETAILED)
# ============================================================

BASE URL: http://localhost:8000
PROTOCOL: HTTP/1.1
CONTENT-TYPE: application/json

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
ENDPOINT 1: POST /predict
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PURPOSE: Real-time anomaly prediction for patient vitals

REQUEST:
────────
Headers:
  Content-Type: application/json
  Authorization: Bearer <token>  (optional, for future auth)

Body (JSON):
{
  "patient_id": "P12345",           // Optional: patient identifier
  "timestamp": "2026-04-18T10:30:45Z",  // Optional: ISO 8601 format
  "vitals": {
    "heart_rate": 85.0,             // Required: beats per minute (40-200)
    "spo2": 96.0,                   // Required: oxygen saturation % (70-100)
    "temperature": 37.2,            // Required: Celsius (35-42)
    "systolic_bp": 120.0,           // Required: mmHg (70-200)
    "diastolic_bp": 80.0            // Required: mmHg (40-130)
  },
  "image_path": "images/ecg_123.jpg",  // Optional: path to medical image
  "history": [                      // Optional: last 60 timesteps for TFT
    {
      "timestamp": "2026-04-18T10:25:45Z",
      "heart_rate": 82.0,
      "spo2": 97.0,
      "temperature": 37.1,
      "systolic_bp": 118.0,
      "diastolic_bp": 78.0
    },
    // ... up to 60 previous readings
  ]
}

RESPONSE (Success - 200 OK):
────────────────────────────
{
  "status": "success",
  "patient_id": "P12345",
  "timestamp": "2026-04-18T10:30:45Z",
  "scores": {
    "tft_score": 0.35,              // TFT model output [0.0-1.0]
    "cnn_score": 0.42,              // CNN model output [0.0-1.0]
    "edge_score": 0.28,             // Edge model output [0.0-1.0]
    "final_score": 0.36             // Weighted fusion result [0.0-1.0]
  },
  "decision": "NORMAL",             // NORMAL | SUSPICIOUS | CRITICAL
  "confidence": 0.92,               // Confidence level [0.0-1.0]
  "action": "No action required",   // Recommended action
  "weights_used": {
    "tft": 0.4,
    "cnn": 0.3,
    "edge": 0.3
  },
  "inference_time_ms": 45.2,        // Total inference latency
  "model_versions": {
    "tft": "v1.0.0",
    "cnn": "v1.0.0",
    "edge": "v1.0.0"
  }
}

RESPONSE (Error - 400 Bad Request):
────────────────────────────────────
{
  "status": "error",
  "error_code": "INVALID_INPUT",
  "message": "Missing required field: vitals.heart_rate",
  "details": {
    "field": "vitals.heart_rate",
    "expected": "float (40-200)",
    "received": null
  }
}

RESPONSE (Error - 500 Internal Server Error):
──────────────────────────────────────────────
{
  "status": "error",
  "error_code": "MODEL_INFERENCE_FAILED",
  "message": "TFT model inference failed",
  "details": {
    "model": "tft",
    "error": "Model file not found: models/tft_model.pth"
  }
}

